   <p><note place="header">405</note>
<lb/><date when="1863-12-22">Dec<hi rend="sup">r</hi>. 22<hi rend="underline"><hi rend="sup">nd</hi></hi> <gap/>3.</date>
<lb/>Gen<hi rend="underline"><hi rend="sup">l</hi></hi> L. Thomas
<lb/>Adjutant General U. S. A.
<lb/>Washington, D. C.
<lb/>General:</p>
<p>I am instructed by the Governor to request that, Private Joseph K. Pitts, Co<hi rend="sup">y</hi>. K. 16<hi rend="underline">"</hi> Ky Infy. be discharged to accept promotion as a Lieutenant in the 45 Ky Infy. his command is in the field.</p>
<p>Resp<hi rend="sup">y</hi>
<lb/>Your obed<hi rend="underline"><hi rend="sup">t</hi></hi> Serv<hi rend="sup">t.</hi>
<lb/><hi rend="underline">John Boyle</hi>
<lb/>Adj<hi rend="sup">t</hi> Gen<hi rend="sup">l</hi> of Ky</p>
